name: Himeko
descHash: The one who repaired the Astral Express. To witness the vast starry sky, she decided to travel with the Astral Express. Her hobby is brewing hand-made coffee.

29328.name: Credit
29328.desc: This currency, used by the Interastral Peace Corporation to settle accounts with its customers, is now widely accepted as the hard currency for space travel.
29328.lore: "People run around fighting and trading for numbers in a terminal, but the truly precious cannot be bought."

125435.name: Tracks of Destiny
125435.lore: Your victory is secured by countless failures, and the small steps you have taken led you to the turning point of fate.

409960.name: Traveler's Guide
409960.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>20,000</nobr> Character EXP.
409960.lore:
Required reading for world exploration. Press the "Read" button to tune in to an attractive voice in a language you understand, telling you about the legendary encounters of renowned adventurers across different worlds as well as the precious wisdom and knowledge that they have gathered.

"All-new series of the Traveler's Guide, The Chef's Manual to Galactic Cuisine, is now available for purchase."
"For submissions, please connect to synesthesia beacon ERD-23θ to contact an Intelligentsia Guild representative. Method of payment can be arranged to your convenience."

409961.name: Adventure Log
409961.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>5000</nobr> Character EXP.
409961.lore:
A neatly organized collection of educational adventure notes containing countless illustrations and texts entailing adventures from beginning to end, as well as valuable information and survival-related techniques.

"Why not just digitize it and save it on a photolith disk? That'd be much more convenient."
"Advanced technology is far more fragile than you'd think when faced with stellar storms and neuron flow eruptions. Besides, I'm sure the author of this book wanted people to read it in the simplest of ways."

409962.name: Travel Encounters
409962.desc: Experience material for characters. Provides <nobr>1000</nobr> Character EXP.
409962.lore:
A travel diary with messy handwriting and random content. It's not of much use to you.

"Dan Heng, hurry up and finish reading it so you can throw it away."

549438.name: Extinguished Core
549438.desc: The heart of a monster wandering the Fragmentum. Crude material used for enhancement.
549438.lore:
It is a lesion that breeds evil, the impulse to sin. It is the source of the Fragmentum distortion.
A heavy blow has caused this heart to stop beating and lose its luster.

"Preliminary tests indicate it's some kind of hybrid: one half is primordial, and the other half is something very similar to Stellarons." — Department of Biology, Sarah Castro
comeFrom: Backwater Pass: Flamespawns or other enemies
Rivet Town: Flamespawns or other enemies

633379.name: Glimmering Core
633379.desc: The heart of a monster wandering the Fragmentum. Normal material used for enhancement.
633379.lore:
It is a lesion that breeds evil, the impulse to sin. It is the source of the Fragmentum distortion.
The heart is glimmering and the veins on it indicate it's still alive.

"What kind of monster is this? Did you see it... Its face! It has the face of our previous leader!"
comeFrom: Backwater Pass: Equilibrium Level 2+ Flamespawns or other enemies
Rivet Town: Equilibrium Level 2+ Flamespawns or other enemies

635675.name: Key of Inspiration
635675.desc: A mythical key that appears in the hands of the Meditative Scholars. Used to level up Traces slightly for Erudition characters.
635675.lore:
It can unlock inspirations hidden deep within the conscience.
To take hold of the key is to grasp at the darting embers of thought that lead to the forward path.

"Eureka!"

717320.name: Squirming Core
717320.desc: The heart of a monster wandering the Fragmentum. Advanced material used for enhancement.
717320.lore:
It is a lesion that breeds evil, the impulse to sin. It is the source of the Fragmentum distortion.
The heart is pulsating slowly, with a residual force powerful enough to cause a new calamity. It's best to destroy it to prevent further troubles.

"It's like a cancer..."
comeFrom: Backwater Pass: Equilibrium Level 4+ Flamespawns or other enemies
Rivet Town: Equilibrium Level 4+ Flamespawns or other enemies

836261.name: Key of Wisdom
836261.desc: A mythical key that appears in the hands of the greatest prodigies of the galaxy. Used to level up Traces significantly for Erudition characters.
836261.lore:
This is the proof of invitation to the halls of the Nous Temple.
Finding the door of which this key opens is a far more arduous task than obtaining the key itself. Those who pass through the doors will immediately realize the impossibility of returning to this side.

"The Erudition does not have answers to the universe, but it will teach you how to ask the right questions."

920202.name: Key of Knowledge
920202.desc: A mythical key that appears in the hands of the sages of the worlds. Used to level up Traces moderately for Erudition characters.
920202.lore:
It can unlock the mysteries binding the truth of the world and grants knowledge beyond the understanding of humans.
No matter how the wielder attempts to display their possession of the key, no one but themselves can see its form. Some people believe that to be a gift from the heavens, while others think it's a sign of mental disorder.

"I had a dream of molecules coiling up into a loop like a snake biting its own tail. I woke up realizing that this is the answer I've been looking for all along!"

983278.name: Endotherm Chitin
983278.desc: Hot, translucent substance almost like fire in the solid state. Can be used for the Ascension of Fire characters.
983278.lore:
Strange chitin peeled off from an interdimensional creature. Although not piping hot anymore, it still radiates warmth.

"It's too cold outside. But with this gemstone on you, you'll be able to travel far and wide, even to search for cities with humans left..."

985668.name: Destroyer's Final Road
985668.lore:
The Leviathan's heart has stopped beating, but its mind lives on despite being trapped in a case. As long as the lid is closed, its mind is simultaneously both alive and dead, driving the engine of destruction.

"Doomsday Beast, a blight made in the Warforge using what's left of a Leviathan and the weeping bones of thousands of the dead. It longs for the destruction of the universe and itself."

ranks.name: Childhood
ranks.descHash: After "Victory Rush" is triggered, Himeko's SPD increases by <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> for <nobr>#2[i]</nobr> turn(s).

ranks.name: Convergence
ranks.descHash: Deals <nobr>#2[i]%</nobr> more DMG to enemies whose HP percentage is <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> or less.

ranks.name: Poised
ranks.descHash:
Skill Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Basic ATK Lv. +1, up to a maximum of Lv. 10.

ranks.name: Dedication
ranks.descHash: When Himeko's Skill inflicts Weakness Break on an enemy, she gains <nobr>#1[i]</nobr> extra point(s) of Charge.

ranks.name: Aspiration
ranks.descHash:
Ultimate Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.
Talent Lv. +2, up to a maximum of Lv. 15.

ranks.name: Trailblaze!
ranks.descHash: Ultimate deals DMG 2 extra times, each of which deals Fire DMG equal to <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> of the original DMG to a random enemy.

skills.name: Sawblade Tuning
skills.descHash: Deals Fire DMG equal to #1[i]% of Himeko's ATK to a single enemy.

skills.name: Molten Detonation
skills.descHash: Deals Fire DMG equal to #1[i]% of Himeko's ATK to a single enemy and Fire DMG equal to #2[i]% of Himeko's ATK to enemies adjacent to it.

skills.name: Heavenly Flare
skills.descHash: Deals Fire DMG equal to #1[i]% of Himeko's ATK to all enemies. Himeko regenerates #2[i] extra Energy for each enemy defeated.

skills.name: Victory Rush
skills.descHash:
When an enemy is inflicted with Weakness Break, Himeko gains 1 point of Charge (max #2[i] points).
If Himeko is fully Charged when an ally performs an attack, Himeko immediately performs 1 follow-up attack and deals Fire DMG equal to #1[i]% of her ATK to all enemies, consuming all Charge points.
At the start of the battle, Himeko gains 1 point of Charge.

skills.name: Attack
skills.descHash: Attack an enemy, and when the battle starts, reduce their Toughness of the corresponding Type.

skills.name: Incomplete Combustion
skills.descHash: After using Technique, creates a dimension that lasts for #4[i] second(s). After entering battle with enemies in the dimension, there is a #1[i]% base chance to increase Fire DMG taken by enemies by #2[i]% for #3[i] turn(s). Only 1 dimension created by allies can exist at the same time.

embedBonusSkill.name: Magma
embedBonusSkill.descHash: Skill deals <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> more DMG to enemies currently afflicted with Burn.

embedBonusSkill.name: Benchmark
embedBonusSkill.descHash: When current HP percentage is <nobr>#1[i]%</nobr> or higher, CRIT Rate increases by <nobr>#2[i]%</nobr>.

embedBonusSkill.name: Starfire
embedBonusSkill.descHash:
After using an attack, there is a #1[i]% base chance to inflict Burn on enemies for #2[i] turn(s).
When afflicted with Burn, enemies take Fire DoT equal to #3[i]% of Himeko's ATK at the start of each turn.

voiceItems.title: First Meeting
voiceItems.text: Welcome aboard, Trailblazer. I'm Himeko, navigator of the Astral Express. I'm sure we're about to embark on a fascinating journey together.

voiceItems.title: Greeting
voiceItems.text: Hey there. Tired? How about a coffee?

voiceItems.title: Parting
voiceItems.text: Relax, Pom-Pom and I are here to take care of the train.

voiceItems.title: About Self: Relationship With the Astral Express
voiceItems.text: The Express and I are like old friends — we've helped each other a lot. I fixed it so that it could get back to its original route, and in return it takes me to unknown frontiers.

voiceItems.title: About Self: Fixing the Express
voiceItems.text: As far as malfunctions on the train are concerned, I've usually dealt with them before you guys even realize anything's amiss.

voiceItems.title: Chat: Final Stop
voiceItems.text: I'm speculating, but I think the Express departs from Akivili's home world and returns there before starting the journey anew. So the Express doesn't have a "final stop" per se — it's up to you where you disembark.

voiceItems.title: Hobbies
voiceItems.text: I have a knack for blending different coffee beans. Can I make you a cup? I recommend not adding milk — black coffee is proper coffee.

voiceItems.title: Annoyances
voiceItems.text: Seems like only Dan Heng has a kind word for my coffee. What do you think? ...Well, I've always thought that bitter is better...

voiceItems.title: Something to Share
voiceItems.text: When people live together it seems like nobody ever changes. Only when they're away from each other for a long time do surprising transformations occur...

voiceItems.title: Knowledge
voiceItems.text: When we scour the universe for the things we seek, most of the time it's less of a "Eureka, I found it!" moment and more of a "Is this it? What if I'm wrong?" moment.

voiceItems.title: About March 7th
voiceItems.text: If I woke up on the Express without any memories, there's no way I'd recover as quickly as March has. I admire her for that, but I also worry about her... If I'm ever too busy, please do take the time to chat with her.

voiceItems.title: About Dan Heng
voiceItems.text: Dan Heng is the cautious type — I think he's gotten used to doing things by himself. He doesn't like to bother or inconvenience others. That's why I asked him to be the train's guard and maintain the data bank. I don't think he'd have joined us if there wasn't anything for him to do.

voiceItems.title: About Welt
voiceItems.text: I think Welt's anxious that he can't keep up with you youngsters, but he sure seems young at heart to me...

voiceItems.title: About Pom-Pom
voiceItems.text: To Pom-Pom, I'll always be the train's mechanic, haha.

storyItems.title: Character Details
storyItems.text:
An adventurous scientist who encountered the Astral Express as a young woman when it got stranded in her homeworld.
Years later, when Himeko finally repairs the Express and begins her journey into the stars, she realized that this is only the beginning. On her journey to trailblaz new worlds, she would need many more companions...
And while they may have different destinations, they all gaze at the same starry sky.
